Class Summary
AllTests  
AverageFilter This #Filter subclass will filter by taking the inputs and calculating the average of previous inputs and that is the output.
AverageTest  
BinomialFilter This class is a special class of the #FIRFilter where the input coefficients are the binomial distribution of from zero to a number N.
CascadeTest  
Filter This abstract class is a basic outline of what makes up all other filters.
FilterCascade This #Filter subclass will take an input #Signal and filter it through all of the filters that are contained within the cascade and the output of the last filter in the cascade is the output of this filter subclass.
FIRFilter This class is a subclass of the #ScalarLinearFilter with a zero output coefficient parameter list.
IdentityFilter The IdentityFilter is a #Filter that will simply output exactly what was input to it.
IdentityTest  
MaxFilter This #Filter subclass will determine the maximum input Signal from the set of previous inputs and that Signal will be the output of this filter.
MaxFilterTest  
MinFilter This #Filter subclass will determine the minimum input #Signal from the set of previous inputs and that #Signal will be the output of this filter.
MinFilterTest  
PureGainFilter This class is a variant of the #FIRFilter that has an input coefficient list that is a single scalar number that will output a #Signal proportional to the input.
ScalarFilter This abstract subclass of #Filter is used to create new variants of filters that are to only take scalar numbers as their input Signal.
ScalarLinearFilter This class is the ScalarLinearFilter and is a subclass of the #ScalarFilter.
ScalarLinearTest  
Signal<T extends Number> The Signal class is used as an intermediary to the Filter classes so that the Filter classes will be able to handle scalars and vectors similarly by handling Signals instead.
